<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id=".E5.BB.B6.E4.BC.B8.E9.98.85.E8.AF.BB_Further_Reading">延伸阅读 Further Reading</span></h2>
<p>　  </p>
<p style="font:bold 150% sans-serif;">医学的现状和中医学的发展<br />
Current State in Medical Studies and the Development in Chinese Medical Studies</p>
<table style="width:100%;background-color:#efefef;border-collapse:collapse;">
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">1</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　时至 21 世纪，中医学迸发的一切光辉已属过去。在现时代，我们需要认真考虑的是中医学在当今条件下的特殊意义及潜在的前瞻性价值，以及我们如何采取积极措施来主动应对中医学面临的一系列机遇和挑战。 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　By 21st century, TCM burst forth in all its glory is in the past. Nowadays, we need to give serious consideration to the special significance of traditional Chinese medicine in today's conditions and potential value of prospective, and how we can take positive steps to take the initiative to deal with a series of opportunities and challenges facing the traditional Chinese medicine.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">2</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>第一节　当今医学的成就与社会的新需求
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>Section 1　 New needs of today's medical achievements and community
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">3</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　结合当今社会的变迁来讨论医学的成就与缺憾，是我们认清21 世纪中医学发展可能趋势的前提。
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Combined with changes in today's society to discuss the achievements and shortcomings of medical, is the premise we recognize the 21st century development trends of Chinese medicine.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">4</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>一、20 世纪医学的成就
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>１．Achievements of 20th century medicine
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">5</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　医学科学和医疗实践在 20 世纪获得了迅速的发展。这表现在多方面：首先，20 世纪才是西方医学的治疗时代。许多疾病的有效治疗和预防，在 20 世纪才真正开始变成现实。有学者宣称：20 世纪每一个 10 年在医疗卫生方面的新进展，要超过以前几十个世纪的成就总和。据估计，仅在 20 世纪中叶，医生挽救的人的生命比有史以来和史前时期所挽救的人的生命总数还要多。有三个指标可以表明本世纪的西方医学在这方面的成就。一个是各种传染病和营养缺乏病在发达国家已被有效控制；鼠疫、疟疾、黄热病、脊髓灰质炎等等已完全失去了让人谈之色变的威风；被历史学家称为“所有死亡使者中最可怕的”天花业已在地球上被消灭。第二是有效药物和防治方法激增。19 世纪末，只有少数几种化学合成药物可供临床选用，而现在，治疗的药库中已发展到数以万计的药物，每年的新药仍层出不穷，抗生素、疫苗、抗心血管病药、抗高血压药、抗糖尿病药、电解质溶液、激素、维生素、激光、化疗，以及公共卫生措施，都大大地提高了人类与疾病抗争的能力。第三是平均寿命显著延长，死亡率大幅度降低。人类平均寿命在 20 世纪延长了约 30 岁，这无疑是人类历史上的一项伟业。 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Medical science and medical practice in the 20th century has obtained a rapid development. Which is reflected in many ways: first, the 20th century is the era of Western medical treatment. Effective treatment and prevention of many diseases, and really started to become a reality only in the 20th century. Some scholars claim that: every 10 in 20th century advances in health, above and beyond the sum for decades, centuries before. It is estimated that only in the middle of the 20th century, doctors save people's lives than history and prehistoric times more total number of saved human lives. Three indicators show that Western medicine in this century's achievements in this regard. A variety of infectious and nutritional deficiency diseases in developed countries has been effectively controlled; plague, malaria, yellow fever, poliomyelitis and so on has been completely lost one on pale's power and prestige; known to historians as "the most terrible of all the Angel of death," smallpox on this planet have been eliminated. Second was an explosion of effective drugs and prevention. In late 19th century, only a handful of chemical synthetic drugs are available for clinical use, and now, drugs to treat the library has grown to tens of thousands of drugs, new drugs each year still grew, Resistance of antibiotics, vaccines, cardiovascular medicine, antihypertensives, antidiabetic drugs, electrolyte, hormones, vitamins, laser, chemotherapy, as well as public health measures, have greatly improved the ability of humans and disease resistance. Third, the average life expectancy is significantly extended, the mortality rate. 20th century extension of about 30 years of age, this is undoubtedly a Albert in human history.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">6</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　其次，医学科学正向纵深与广袤两极发展。在纵深方面，医学研究已进入了真正的基因时代，基因结构组学与功能组学研究，不断揭示出生命科学领域最细微的本质特点。它的一系列科学成就若能真正转化为实际应用，预计十年乃至几十年后，人们将第一次有可能针对性地解决包括遗传性疾病在内的许多难治性疾病的防治问题。另一方面，医学科学又向广袤拓展，或曰“回归医学”、“呼唤人性的医学”，强调社会－心理－生物医学模式，以及心身医学，行为医学，社会医学等分支学科的迅速发展，鲜明地昭示了这一点。 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Secondly, medical science is to develop in depth and vast polar. In terms of depth, medical researchers have entered the real genetic age, group and functional analysis of the gene structure, constantly reveals the nature of the most subtle features in the life sciences. A series of scientific achievement if we can really turn it into practical applications, ten years or even decades later, it is possible for the first time targeted to solve many intractable diseases, including hereditary disease prevention issues. The other hand, to the vast expansion of medical science, or "return to medicine", "appealing for human nature in medicine" and stressed the socio-psycho-biomedical model, Psychosomatic Medicine, Behavioral Medicine, community medicine, such as rapid development of branches, vividly demonstrates this point.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">7</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　再者，医学科学汲取其他科学知识和技术手段的能力大大加强。现在的西方医学，从严格意义上说，已不再是一门单独的学科，物理、化学、植物、工程等的几乎所有的进步和成就都有可能渗透进医学，为医学所用，促进医学及医疗的发展。而且，这种渗透的速度之快使我们看到了医学和医疗领域新的技术和方法层出不穷，琳琅满目，这也导致了医学研究和医疗领域的开支直线攀升，医学分支学科的不断涌现。
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Furthermore, medical science's ability to learn from other scientific knowledge and technical means greatly enhanced. Now, Western medicine, in the strict sense, is no longer a separate discipline, physical, chemical, plant, works almost all of the progress and achievements are likely to infiltrate medical, for medical use, and promote the development of medical and health care. Moreover, this penetration speed so that we can see the proliferation of medical science and new technologies and methods in the field, feast for the eyes, it causes in medical research and healthcare spending, linear climb, branch of medicine continue to emerge.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">8</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>二、21 世纪世界的新需求 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>２．New needs of the 21st century world
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">9</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　近三十多年来，世界发生了巨大的变化，这种变化很难一一罗列，只能就其总体作些分析。我们认为，近三十年来的现时代，区别于以往任何一个时代的本质特征有以下这些：当代人类及其社会已为跨入信息时代而正在进行政治结构、经济实力、科学知识、技术手段、精神文化的多方面准备。该时代趋势有其特定的背景，有学者把这个背景表述为四大客观压力和四大主观需求。 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　For more than 30 years, the world has undergone tremendous changes, this change is hard to list one by one, some analysis only in relation to its overall. We believe that nearly 30 years of age, the difference in the past, the defining characteristic of any period following these: contemporary human society entered the information age and the ongoing political structure, economy, science, technology, spiritual and cultural aspects of preparation. The trend of the times has a specific background, an academic background as the four pressure four subjective and objective needs.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">10</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　（一）当今世界承受的四大客观压力有：
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　（１）In today's world the four objective pressure are:
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">11</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　人口过量——世界人口急剧膨胀，地球相对过载，很快将不堪重负； 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Excessive population--the world's population, rapidly expanding, overloading the Earth will soon be overwhelmed;
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">12</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　资源紧缺——正常消费与非正常消费（浪费）并存，能源、水源、各种不可再生性资源等出现全线紧张、匮乏； 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Resource constraints-the normal consumption and irregular consumption (wasting) coexist, such as energy, water, and a variety of non-renewable resources appear across the Board lack tension;
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">13</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　生态失调——工业文明衍生出环境污染，公害蔓延，自然生态受到严重破坏，地球上已找不到一块纯粹的净土了；一部警世片《后天》，表达了人们对此由衷的担忧； 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Dysbiosis-industrial civilization derived from environmental pollution, pollution spread, ecological devastation, has not found a piece of pure land on Earth; a cautionary movie of the day after tomorrow, and expressed heartfelt concern;
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">14</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　战乱持续——暴力事件频繁，局部争端和战事困扰人类，恐怖活动与宗教战争日显频繁，“911”事件、中东、巴尔干、伊拉克等均是实例，世界无法安宁；军费负担和无辜死亡的社会及生存压力已让人类无法承受。
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Frequent violent incidents of the war, local disputes and war afflicting humankind, growing frequent terrorist activities and religious wars, the "911" incident, the Middle East, the Balkans, Iraq, is an instance, the world cannot be tranquillity; social and stress of the military burden and death of innocent people cannot afford.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">15</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　此外，无论是发达国家还是发展中国家，都面临着严重的经济发展压力。现时代的种种客观压力导致了人类身心始终处于高度应激状态，社会生活节奏加快，紧张、焦虑、恐慌等一系列因素引发了疾病谱和死亡谱的根本性改变。许多文明病和身心疾病与日俱增，各种健康危险因素，如文化、个人行为、性格特征、紧张状态、吸烟、吸毒、酗酒、家庭瓦解等构成人类健康的主要威胁。所有这些，都使得卫生保健事业难度加大，传统生物医学方法常捉襟见肘，无法从容应对。 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　In addition, both developed and developing countries, are facing severe economic pressures. Objective of modern pressures led to the human body and mind always in a State of high stress, the pace of social life, stress, anxiety, panic and a series of factors are responsible for the death of disease spectrum and spectrum of fundamental change. Many civilization diseases and mental and physical illnesses is increasing, health risk factors, such as culture, personal behaviors, personality traits, stress, smoking, drug and alcohol abuse, family breakdown, and so pose a major threat to human health. All of this makes health care more difficult, Conventional biomedical methods always tight, unable to deal with.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">16</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　（二）当代人类提出的四大主观需求是： 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　（２）Humanity's four subjective needs are:
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">17</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　劳动过程省力化——要求解除或减轻笨重的体力劳动，缩短工作时间；
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Labour process of energy-saving--for the lifting or reduction of heavy manual labor, reduced hours of work;  
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">18</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　知识财富平均化——要求普及教育、文化和科学，共享知识的科技成果； 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Knowledge wealth--requires universal access to education, culture and science, knowledge sharing scientific and technological achievements;
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">19</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　政治、经济生活民主化——要求更多的参与，增强政府决策的透明度，反对专制，谋求南北贸易平等，消除东西方经济壁垒，实行南南经济合作； 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Political democratization, economic life--demanded more participation, and enhance transparency in Government decision-making, against the autocracy, pursuit of North-South trade equality, eliminate economic barriers between East and West, the implementation of South-South economic cooperation;
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">20</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　生活质量高级化——要求在温饱基础上实现物质生活和精神生活富裕、舒适。 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　High--quality of life requires on the basis of material and spiritual wealth, comfort food and clothing.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">21</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　根据马斯洛需求层次的理论，人类第一级的需求是生理上的，第二级是安全需求，第三级为社会需求，第四级是心理上的需求……。随着文明的进步，生活质量的提高，人类对卫生保健的要求也越来越高。以我国为例，由于全国人民已从温饱型过渡到小康型生活水平，广大民众不再仅仅以医疗满足治疗机体疾病的需要，还要求预防疾病，进行心理诊断和治疗，提高生存质量、有效地延长生存期限，以及增进健康。表现为医疗卫生服务需求进一步扩大，即从治疗扩大到病前干预，健康维护、健康促进、疾病预防以及病后调养等的一系列服务，从生理治疗扩大到心理卫生服务，从院内扩大到院外服务，从技术扩大到社会服务，人们的价值观也相应地发生了变化，例如过去吃饱即可心满意足，现在要求吃的花色品种多样，又合乎营养要求，还需要各种保健食品、滋补药膳、各种饮料，甚至特种食品如低胆固醇食品、无糖糖果等。 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　According to Maslow's hierarchy of needs theory, on the first level of human needs are physiological, second-tier security demands, level for social needs, demands of the fourth level is psychologically....... As civilization advances, improved quality of life, human health requirements have become more sophisticated. In China, for example, national transition from food and clothing to a well-off standard of living of the people, the general population not just to medical treatment of diseases of the body's needs are met, but also disease prevention, diagnosis and treatment of mental, improve quality of life, and effectively extend the life and improve health. Performance for medical health service needs further expanded, that from treatment expanded to disease Qian intervention, health maintenance, and health promotion, and disease prevention and disease Hou nursed back to, of series service, from physiological treatment expanded to psychological health service, from homes within expanded to homes outside service, from technology expanded to social service, people of values also corresponding to occurred has changes, such as past eat full can satisfied, now requires eat of Berliner varieties diverse, and is nutrition requires, also needs various health food, and tonic medicinal, and various beverage, Even low cholesterol foods, specialty foods such as sugar-free candies.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">22</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　（三）当代社会变革对医学造成的压力： 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　（３）Contemporary social changes, the pressure medicine:
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">23</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　加速人类疾病构成（疾病谱）的改变，进而推动医学的嬗变，并引起医学研究方向和重点的转移。 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Accelerated human disease form (disease) changes, thus promoting the evolution of medicine and caused the shift of the direction and focus of medical research.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">24</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　人的价值将进一步提升，社会对医学的要求明显提高，要求提供更高质量的治疗，注意病前状态的处理，致力于提高人类人口素质、生活质量和帮助延年益寿，医学的社会职能将进一步扩大。 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　People will further enhance the value of, social medicine improved, seeking higher-quality treatment, pay attention to state before the disease, is committed to improving the quality of human populations, quality of life and help prolong life, the social function of the medicine will be further expanded.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">25</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　促进人类保健模式的改变。世界卫生组织（WHO）曾就此作出过规划，力争在世纪之交达到“人人享受保健”的目标。美国学者麦克斯门预测，到本世纪初，卫生事业中人员的比例，“医生中心”将由上世纪 80 时代的 80％降至 10％，而“保健中心”则由目前的 20％升高到 88％……。所有这些，迫使医学科学和医疗卫生事业必须作出相应的、带有某些特质的调整，否则将无法适应社会所提出的要求。 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Promoting human health patterns change. The World Health Organization (WHO) has made plans to propel the century reached "health for all" goal. United States scholar Max predicted, by the beginning of this century, staff ratios in the health services, "Medical Center" from the era of the late 80 's to 80% per cent, while "health centres" from the current level of 20% rises to cent ... .... All of these, forcing medical sciences and medical and health services must make corresponding adjustments, with some traits of, otherwise will not be able to accommodate the request of the community.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">26</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>三、生物学的境遇与科学哲学的反思
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>３． Reflection on the plight of biology and philosophy of science
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">27</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　广义而言，医学就其自然科学部分而言，仍属生物学范畴。生物学，或曰：生物科学，生命科学。数百年来，一直滞后于物理科学（广义的是指除生命科学以外的其他自然科学）。20 世纪中后叶，由于科学发展本身遇到了问题，以及科学哲学的反思，生物学发展的相关问题又一次被提了出来，其有关讨论与中医学的命运不无关系。 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Broadly, the medicine in terms of its Science section remains of biological study. Biology or biological science, life sciences. For hundreds of years, has been lagging in physical science (broadly refers to the other natural sciences, except for life sciences). After the mid-20th century, due to scientific development itself had a problem, as well as reflections on the philosophy of science, biology-related issues came up again, and its discussions on the fate of Chinese medicine are not unrelated.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">28</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　讨论的核心是生物科学与物理科学的关系。以往西方人士中占主导地位的观点总认为：生物科学属于物理科学的一个分支，用物理学的各种方法足以研究生物学问题，揭示生命根源与疾病的种种奥秘。这一观念认为实体结构决定一切，还原方法足以研究所有的自然现象，这充分体现在西方现代生物医学的一系列研究成果特别是分子生物学，基因组学等的研究之中。然而，生物学研究的捉襟见肘，以及诸如现代进化论，遗传学，群组生物学，包括体质医学，心身医学的研究进展，都对传统的生物医学提出了挑战。
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Central to the discussion is the relationship between physical science and biological science. Dominated by Westerners in the past always thought: Biological Sciences belongs to a branch of physical science, using various methods to study biological problems of physics, reveal the source of life and all the mysteries of the disease. The notion that physical structure determines everything, restoring enough to institute some natural phenomenon, which fully reflected in a series of Western modern biomedical research results, in particular molecular biology and genomics research. However, biology research to make ends meet, as well as the modern theory of evolution, genetics, biology of group, Including physical medicine, advances in Psychosomatic Medicine, challenges the traditional biomedical.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">29</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　生命现象就是物理化学现象吗？用还原方法，把生命现象还原为物理化学过程，能说明所有问题吗？据此，学者们分成两大派：一派回答肯定，被视为“分支派”，（即生物学属于物理学的分支）；另一派回答“否”，他们认为，生物现象是独特的自然现象，生物科学相对于物理科学其内容有自主性，而这些自主性揭示生物现象的关键，用还原方法只能揭示部分。这一派被称为“自主派”。而后者与中医学的研究思路与方法有着某些“神似”之处。从科学哲学角度，分支派更多地属于“后实证主义”者，而“自主派”多属“反实证主义”者。在此，不便对两派作出详细评价（较详内容可参见《中医学方法论》教材），只想指出一点，中医学的发展就自然科学与科学哲学而言，亦有其相当的时空有利背景。 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Physical chemistry of life is finding? Restore methods, and to restore life to the physico-chemical processes, all questions? Accordingly, scholars were into two big sent: faction answered certainly, was considered "branch sent", (that biology belonging to physics of branch); another faction answered "whether", they think, bio phenomenon is unique of natural phenomenon, bio science relative Yu physical science its content has autonomous sexual, and these autonomous sexual reveals bio phenomenon of key, with restore method only reveals part. This school is known as "independent school". Research thinking and method of TCM and the latter has a certain "likeness" of the Department. From the perspective of philosophy of science, branches more belonging to "post positivism", and "independent" are "anti-positivist". This inconvenience to make a detailed evaluation of the two factions (more details can be found in the methodology of traditional Chinese medicine textbook), just wanted to point out that the development of Chinese medicine in terms of science and philosophy of science, there are quite favourable background of time and space.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">30</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>第二节 现代社会的健康难题
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>Section 2　 Modern societies health problems
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">31</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　历史的进步是一把双刃剑，巨大的成就每每与难解的问题相伴而行。现代医学从根本上改变了人类医学的进化图景，改善了人类的卫生和保健状况。然而，它同样面临着一系列严重问题。 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　The progress of history is a double-edged sword, great achievements and difficult problems. Modern medicine has fundamentally changed the evolutionary picture of human medicine, improving the State of human health and health care. However, it also faces a number of serious problems.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">32</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>一、现代瘟疫 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>１．Modern plague
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">33</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　疾病的历史差不多和有机生命的历史一样久远，人类医学的最为悲壮的色彩或许在于：人类自以为可以控制一种又一种疾病，可是命中注定无法完全消灭疾病。21 世纪的“瘟疫“主要有： 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Disease history almost as long as history of organic life, the most tragic overtones may lie in human medicine: human beings who think they can control a disease, but fate could not be completely eliminated the disease. Of the 21st century "plague" are mainly as follows:
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">34</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　（一）生活方式病：纯生物医学的盲区 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　（１）Lifestyle: a pure biomedical dead zone
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">35</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　恶性肿瘤、心血管病、脑血管病，以及以糖尿病为代表的代谢性疾病等已成为人类目前的主要死亡因素和临床最常见的健康危害，在上海它们分别列医学疾病谱和死亡谱的前 1、2、3、5 位，因此而死亡者约占了总死亡人数的 7 成。其中，2000 年的癌症发病率每年已高达约十万分之三百，而且仍在快速增长之中。然而，令人忧虑的是若仍囿于原有的纯生物医学模式，在可以预见的将来，上述这些疾病的防治将难以获得突破性进展，因为它们不只是一类生物学上的异常。
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Malignant tumors, cardiovascular diseases, cerebrovascular diseases, as well as metabolic diseases, such as is represented by the diabetes has become the main factors of death and the most common health hazards, respectively in Shanghai medical ailments and deaths Spectra ex 1, 2, 3, 5, died about 70% per cent of the total number of deaths. Among them, the 2000 annual incidence of cancer have up to about three hundred out of 10,000, and is still growing rapidly. However, the worrying is if it is confined to the original pure biomedical model, in the foreseeable future, the prevention and treatment of these diseases would be difficult to secure breakthrough, Because they are not only a kind of unusual in biology.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">36</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　精神障碍性疾病的发病率本来就相当高，尚无可靠的化学药物治疗和预防其发展和复发，如今，由于竞争加剧，人际关系紧张，它又扶摇直上，发病率继续增高。如从上世纪 70 年代末到世纪之交的 20 年间，北京市的精神分裂症患病率上升了 5.1 倍，上海市上升了 5.3 倍；有些大城市的抑郁症发病率超过 4%，加上隐匿型抑郁症或尚未寻求医学帮助的抑郁症患者，估计总患病人数可高达 10%。丹麦 1979 年报告的躁狂抑郁性精神病患病率已达 20%。与此同时，“紧张状态”和心身疾患日益严重。据统计，某些国家综合医院门诊初诊患者中，2/3 左右与此有关。 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　The incidence of mental disorders was quite high, there is no reliable chemical drugs in treating and preventing recurrence of their development and, today, due to increased competition, interpersonal tensions, it has soared in the incidence continues to increase. From the late 70 to the 20 years of the century, rose 5.1 times the prevalence of schizophrenia in Beijing, Shanghai increased 5.3 times times over 4% incidence of depression in some major cities, coupled with latent depression or have not sought medical help in patients with depression, estimate the total number of patients may be as high as 10%. Denmark reported in 1979 had reached 20% the prevalence of manic depressive psychosis. Meanwhile, the "tension" and psychosomatic disorders is becoming increasingly serious. According to statistics, the first visit out-patients in general hospitals in selected countries, around two-thirds was involved.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">37</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　（二）新老传染病肆虐 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　（２）New and old infectious
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">38</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　不久前，人们还在庆幸，现代医学以纯生物技术“攻克”了许多传染病，使之灭绝。然而，话音未落，灾难便起。一方面，旧的传染病纷纷死灰复燃，例如，结核病，80 年代末人们为将其控制而欢跃，到了 90 年代中叶，全球每年死于结核病者又高达300 万。我国 90 年代中后期，每年新发结核病人超过 60 万。又如性病、疟疾，白喉等，都大有卷土重来之势。特别是性病，这个一度曾在中国彻底灭绝了的“肮脏”疾病，现有患病人数不下千万；而中国的乙型肝炎患者也将以千万计。因此，传染病仍构成了对健康的巨大威胁。据 1999 年统计，全球下呼吸道感染约造成 400 万人死亡，感染引起的腹泻导致 220 万人死亡。
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　 Not long ago, people still celebrate, modern medicine with pure biotech "captured" many infectious diseases and make it extinct. However, volleying, a disaster. One hand, the resurgence of old infectious diseases, such as tuberculosis, Viiv for its control in the late 80, 90 's, worldwide die each year from TB in turn up to 3 million. 90 at late stage new TB more than 600,000 people each year. Such as sexually transmitted diseases, malaria, diphtheria, great comeback trend. In particular, sexually transmitted diseases, the once worked in China for complete extermination of the "dirty" disease No less than do existing prevalence; hepatitis b patients in China will also be millions. Therefore, infectious diseases still poses a great threat to health. According to 1999 statistics, of lower respiratory tract infection caused about 4 million deaths in the world, infections resulting in 2.2 million deaths caused by diarrhea.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">39</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　更令人不安的是，新的传染病不断涌现。近 20 年来已发现有 30 多种新发传染病。其中 2003 年肆虐的 SARS，让大半个中国半年时间内几乎人人陷于惶恐不安之窘境。2004 年初的禽流感又闹得整个世界不安宁，几十亿只无辜的家禽惨遭杀戮。其他如埃伯拉病毒、疯牛病、口蹄疫、0139 型霍乱，也都让人谈之色变，造成一阵阵世界性恐慌。特别是艾滋病，中国的患者已近90 万，世界已超过 4200 万，2000 年已造成 2000 多万人死亡。谓其为瘟疫，毫不为过。而这些现代超级瘟疫，大多非单纯的生物医学方法，包括抗生素类所能控制，这更加剧了灾难性后果的严重性。
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Even more disturbing is that new infectious diseases are emerging. Almost 20 years there is about more than 30 new infectious diseases have been identified. In 2003 the SARS epidemic, half of China within half a year almost everyone was in panic embarrassment. Avian flu in early 2004 and got no peace in the world as a whole, the brutal killing of poultry in billions of innocent. Others such as aibola virus, mad cow disease, foot and mouth disease, cholerae 0139, let people with pale, caused a worldwide panic. In particular AIDS, patients in China has nearly 900,000, the world has more than 42 million, In 2000, has killed more than 20 million people. His plague, not much. These modern Super plague that mostly not purely biomedical methods, including antibiotics can control, which aggravated the severity of catastrophic consequences.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">40</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>二、遗传性疾病居高不下
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>２．Hereditary diseases remain high
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">41</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　遗传性疾病已发现有 3000 多种。环境的改变尤其是污染的加剧，生活方式的变迁，使得遗传病这一暂时尚无良方治疗的疾病发生率还在不断增高之中。 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Hereditary diseases have been found to have more than 3,000 species. Changed circumstances in particular, increased pollution, changes in lifestyle, genetic diseases that currently there is no recipe for treating disease incidence has steadily increased.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">42</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>三、现代社会病
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>３．Modern social disease
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">43</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　许多疾病与现代社会生活有着密切的关系。例如，环境污染导致大量公害病蔓延。西南某地因炼汞，导致了几万人的致畸、致残、致死…….。吸烟、酗酒、吸毒、自杀、凶杀、不良饮食习惯和营养结构等人类行为不仅带来社会问题，亦威胁着人类健康。美国近来的调查表明，50%左右患者死于不良行为，国内亦有调查表明，死于不良行为者在我国高达 44%。仅吸烟一项，21世纪初每年就导致约 140 万中国人死亡。据预测到 2010 年，中国人因吸烟而死亡者每年将高达 200 万人，其中，绝大多数是中壮年人。 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Many diseases has a close relationship with modern life. For example, environmental pollution-causing high spread of the disease. Southwest mercury smelting, caused the teratogenicity of tens of thousands of people, maiming, death...... Smoking, alcoholism, drug abuse, suicide, murder, bad eating habits and trophic structure of human behavior not only bring about social problems also threaten human health. United States recent surveys have shown that about 50% patients died from bad behavior, national survey shows that died of bad actors in our country up to 44%. Smoking only one item, has led to approximately 1.4 million Chinese deaths every year in the early 21st century. As predicted by 2010, the Chinese deaths of up to 2 million people each year because of smoking, which is mostly men. 
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">44</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　一些被污染的食品或有害食品也造成了严重的健康危害，2004 年的阜阳奶粉事件就是典型实例。 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>Some contaminated food or bad food poses a serious health hazard, in 2004 the Fuyang milk powder incident is a typical example.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">45</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>四、其他的健康问题 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>４．Other health problems
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">46</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　除了上述疾病问题外，其他一些社会问题也给医学带来了冲击： 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　In addition to the above problems, and other social issues also brought medicine, came as a shock:
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">47</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　（一）人口造成的健康问题 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　（１）Health problems caused by population
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">48</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　在“人口爆炸”面前，如何控制人口增长、提高人口素质，对于全世界尤其是发展中国家，是一个十分紧迫的问题； 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　"Population explosion" before it, how to control population growth and improve population quality, world-wide, particularly in developing countries, is a matter of urgency;  
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">49</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　平均寿命延长，以至许多国家面临着老龄化问题，老年、中老年性痴呆，老年肿瘤、老年骨质疏松症等，发病率皆高。老年人的保健和生活问题，也是各国卫生部门的紧迫课题……。 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Longer life expectancies, that many countries face ageing, older, senile dementia, tumors in the elderly, senile osteoporosis, incidence is high. Health care for the elderly and problems of life, is also among health sector urgent task......
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">50</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　（二）新的健康危险因素 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　（２）New risk factors for health
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">51</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　现代瘟疫的病因与过去的传染病病因不同，除了生物学因素外，与社会的、心理的、行为的因素关涉更大。健康危险因素是一个社会医学概念，指各种使疾病或死亡发生的可能性增加的因素，具有潜伏期长、特异性低、联合作用强、多因多果、广泛存在等作用特点。健康危险一般分为四类：①生活方式和行为――不良生活习惯、消费和求医不当、有害于健康的业余活动、职业性危害等；②环境因素――人类群体或个体的不良自然环境、身体环境、心理环境和社会环境；③人类生物学因素――成熟和老化、遗传基因、复合内因；④保健服务因素――包括医疗、预防、康复服务，如医疗水平低、初级保健网不健全、卫生经费过少和分配不合理、轻视预防和康复等等。这些因素中很多属于新出现的问题。
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Modern plague causes infectious etiology different from the past, in addition to biological factors, social, psychological, behavioural factors concerning greater. Health risk factors is a concept of community medicine, refers to a variety of factors that increase the likelihood of illness or death occur, has a long incubation period, the combined effect of low specificity, strong, mainly because of fruit characteristics, widespread effects. Health risks is generally divided into four categories: ① lifestyle and acts—bad life habits, and consumption and seeking improper, and harmful Yu health of amateur activities, and career sexual against,; ② environment factors —human groups or individual of bad natural environment, and body environment, and psychological environment and social environment; ③ human biology factors —mature and aging, and genetic gene, and composite internal; ④ health service factors — including medical, and prevention, and rehabilitation service, as medical level low, and primary health network not sound, and health funding too little and distribution not reasonable, and despise prevention and rehabilitation wait. Many of these factors are emerging problems.  
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">52</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　（三）滥用药物
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　（３）Drug abuse 
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">53</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　所有化学合成药物以及部分手术操作和治疗方法等，都有着利弊两重性。过度依赖医药及某些疗法，特别是滥用药物，可导致严重的健康危害。本世纪最大的药物灾难和抗生素的日渐失效便是典型例证。 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　All synthetic drugs as well as some surgery and treatment methods, and so on, there are pros and cons of dual nature. Relying too much on medicines and therapies, in particular the abuse of drugs, can lead to serious health risks. This century's biggest drug disaster and failure of antibiotics is a typical example.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">54</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　50－60 年代，欧洲许多国家使用反应停（酞胺哌嘧酮）作为孕妇的镇静止痛药，认为它安全、有效、无毒。实际上它有导致畸胎、多发性神经炎的严重副作用，流行后很快就引发了本世纪规模最大的最悲惨的药物灾难。据医学家估计，自 1956 年出售后的 6 年间，仅西德就曾引起 6000～8000 例畸胎。据统计美国每年有约 250 万人死于滥用药物，在中国这一问题将更为严重，仅就药物性耳聋而言，中国因滥用链霉素等肾毒性药物所导致的终生性耳聋及声哑患者就高达 1800 万，这是多么可怕的结局。 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　50-60 era, many European countries the use of Thalidomide (the effects of piperidine azoxystrobin ketone) as a sedative and a painkiller of pregnant women, arguing that it is safe and effective, nontoxic. Actually it has serious side effect of causing teratomas, multiple neuritis, popular soon led to largest this century's worst drugs disaster. According to medical scientists estimate that since 1956, went on sale for 6 years, only West Germany gave rise to teratomas in 6000~8000 cases. According to statistics United States about 2.5 million people die each year from drug abuse in China, this issue more seriously, just for the drug-induced deafness, China's abuse of the renal toxicity of Streptomycin and other drugs as a result of a lifetime of deaf and dumb patients up to 18 million, which is what a terrible ending.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">55</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　抗生素是治疗传染性疾病的“奇迹药物”。在全世界范围内抗生素越用越广之际，研究者提出了警告：这些药物正在因为胡使滥用而失去其抗病的原有威力，而其毒副作用却丝毫未见收敛。过去一度对抗生素非常敏感的致病菌，现在却演变出新的抗药菌株。以前一用抗生素即可治愈的疾病，现在却迁延难治，在用药情况下仍然继续传播。这些难题不仅涉及药物，也使人们对以直截了当地对抗、替代等为主的治疗思想的主导性的地位，提出了质疑。 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Antibiotics to treat infectious diseases "miracle drugs". Occasion of the antibiotics used more widely throughout the world, the researchers had warned: these drugs are as lost its original resistance to abuse power, and its side effects but without convergence. Once very sensitive to antibiotics of pathogenic bacteria, now evolved a new drug-resistant strains. Used to a disease that can be cured with antibiotics, but deferment of refractory, in drug cases continued spreading. These problems involve not only drugs, also makes it a straightforward confrontation, alternative treatments, such as ideology and dominant position, have raised questions.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">56</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　人们总幼稚地相信“钱可买来药，从而带来健康”，而药物又是颇能用来赚钱的商品，制造商和推销者会很容易以极有诱惑力的方式号召人们大量使用药物，所以，滥用药物现象将愈演愈烈。半个世纪前，就有医学家不无忧心地说：“医师们的首要任务，是教育群众不要依赖医药。”今天，还要补充一句：“必须教育医生，不要开不必要的处方。”同时，还有必要适当地校正用药的指导思想。 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　People are so naive as to believe that "money can buy medicine, which leads to health", while the drug could be used to make money products, manufacturers and pushers can easily in a very seductive way called for extensive use of drugs, so that drug abuse is growing. Half a century ago, a physician noted with concern that: "the primary mission of the doctors, is to educate the masses not to rely on medicine. "Today, would also like to add that:" the need to educate doctors, get out of unnecessary prescriptions. "At the same time, also need to appropriately correcting the medication guidelines.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">57</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　（四）生命伦理的困境 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>（４）Dilemma of bioethics
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">58</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　自上世纪 60 年代以来，随着医学科学一系列新成果的应用，西方医学界和伦理学界出现了一股研究与医学、生命有关的各种伦理问题的热潮。20 世纪中期以来，几乎每一项重大医学成就都伴随着尖锐的伦理争端，生命伦理学取代传统的医学伦理学的趋势应运而生。 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Since the late 60 's, with the application of a series of new achievements of medical science, Western ethics of the medical profession and the community went on a unit study and popularity of various ethical issues related to medicine, life. The middle of 20th century, almost every major medical achievements are accompanied by acute ethical disputes, replace traditional medical ethics bioethics trends have emerged.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">59</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　涉及伦理学讨论的医学事件和成就主要有：器官移植、安乐死、肿瘤患者的生存权与知情权、试管婴儿、体外受精、人工非自然性交授精、重组 DNA、人体实验、生和死的认定、生命本质的解说、生命质量控制、行为控制、人工流产、计划生育等等。美国生活杂志记者评论生命伦理学时说：“现在(生命伦理)已成为民族问题中的当务之急，这是在生和死、医学道德上，进退两难的最普遍的事例。它们每天苦恼着我们，以致时而轻度痛苦的私事中，时而在像里根的报告以及公众的强烈要求中，都展开了一场恰当有益的，对人类生存艰难选择的思考活动。”
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>Incidents involving medical ethics discussions and achievements are: tumor patients with organ transplantation, euthanasia, right to life and the right to know, in vitro fertilization, IVF, artificial insemination of unnatural sex, recombinant DNA, the human experiment, found that between life and death, the explanation of the essence of life, and the life quality control, behavioral control, abortion, birth control, and so on. United States life magazine reporter commenting on bioethics, said: "now (Bioethics) has become a national issue a top priority, it is in terms of life and death, medical ethics, and dilemma of the most common examples. They upset us every day, Sometimes mild pain in personal, sometimes as Ronald Reagan's report and the public's demand, has embarked on an appropriately helpful, tough choice of activities to human existence. ”  
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">60</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　（五）伪科学的泛滥
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　（５）Pseudoscience flooding  
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">61</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　科学创新的胚芽和伪科学的怪胎，有时是极难辨别的。科学在 20 世纪已成为一个令人羡慕的职业，科学家的社会地位和收入同过去相比已是天壤之别。庸医和骗术，在人类医学史上，不绝于史书。现代医学的巨大发展并未消除它们，反而甚嚣尘上。其中原因不难理解，一是患者受“早日康复”的愿望驱使，难免“急病乱投医”，以致容易造成轻信；二是许多疾病不经治疗可自行消失；三是现代的不少疾病乃精神心理因素所致。所有这些，给江湖医生、医学骗子、骗术、假药等以可乘之机。美国学者在《冒充科学的邪门左道》（中译为《西医伪科学种种》）一书中从医学迷信、江湖医生、养生怪论等角度描绘了西方医学领域中的形形色色的伪科学。在中国，这类情况同样严重，甚至更为猖獗。
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Germ freaks of pseudoscience and scientific innovation, it is sometimes very difficult to distinguish. Science in the 20th century has become an enviable career scientists ' social status and income than in the past are worlds apart. Quacks and con, in the history of human medicine, has never stopped in the history books. Great development of modern medicine has not removed them, but rife. One reason is easy to understand, first, patients "get well soon" driven by desire, inevitably "fumble" so easily gullible; the second is that many diseases do not disappear without treatment; three are modern diseases are caused by psychological factors. All of these, Rivers and lakes, such as doctors, medical fraud, scams, counterfeit drugs to exploit. United States scholars in pretending to be science's scary road to the left (translated as the pseudoscience of all of Western medicine) in his book superstition, quacks, and health from medicine weird remarks in terms of depicting the pseudoscience of all sorts in the field of Western medicine. In China, such cases as serious, even more rampant.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">62</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>第三节 现代中医学面面观
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>Section 3 Aspects of modern traditional Chinese medicine
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">63</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　中医学是一个复杂的知识及技术体系，在新的历史条件下，她有着许多欠缺，又具备着一些发展的契机。如何结合社会需求及医学发展趋势，扬长避短，将一些有价值的发展契机，催化为现实的医学进步，这是放在每个中医工作者面前的神圣任务。而这一切，首先有待于进行冷静、理智的中医学现状分析，并基此作出全方位的，带有前瞻性的评估与预测。 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Knowledge is a complex and technical system of traditional Chinese medicine, under the new historical conditions, and she has many gaps, possessing a number of development opportunities. How to combine the needs of society and medical trends, weaknesses, some valuable development opportunity, catalyzed by the reality of medical progress, it is a sacred task put in front of each of the practitioners of traditional Chinese medicine. And all this, first of all, to be calm, rational analysis of traditional Chinese medicine, and based on those degrees, with a forward-looking estimates and projections.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">64</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>一、中医学的潜在优势
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>１．The potential advantages of traditional Chinese medicine 
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">65</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　就总体而言，在现时代，中医学有着以下一些利于自身发展的因素： 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Generally speaking, modern, traditional Chinese medicine is conducive to the development of the following factors:  
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">66</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　着眼于整体和身心合一等较为正确的观念； 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Focusing on overall physical and psychological unity and more accurate concepts;
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">67</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　医学模式的主导精神是合理的，与未来医学模式有着内在的吻合； 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Leading spirit of the medical model is reasonable and consistent with the medical model of the future is intrinsically;
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">68</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　在方法论方面有着一些潜在的优势，其中有些方法也许能弥补现代生命科学研究之不逮； 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　In terms of methodology has some potential advantages, some of which may be able to compensate for the modern life sciences are not caught;
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">69</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　对于医学现象有着细微的描述，形成了一些独到的理论认识或假说，其中，有些涉及了人们尚未深入加以探究的领域，如气功、针灸、经络、传统药物作用、身心关系等； 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Medicine there is a fine description of the phenomenon, formed the original theories or hypotheses, which, some people have not been deeply explored areas, such as the Qi Gong, acupuncture, Meridian, the role of traditional medicine, physical and mental relationship;
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">70</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　诊治技术方面的众多长处及两千年来积累成的临症丰富经验； 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
<p>　　Diagnosis and treatment of many strengths in technology and accumulation of 2000 years of Pro experience;
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr><td style="width:2%;background-color:#fff;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.7em">71</td>
<td style="width:38%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:1em">
<p>　　在一些边缘学科或新兴分支领域，通过不自觉的实践探索所获得的一些颇有价值的经验和知识； 
</p>
</td><td style="width:1%;background-color:#fff"></td><td style="width:49%;padding:2px 10px;vertical-align:top;font-size:0.85em">
